         <div type="translation">
            <ab>[Year ..] of Imperator Caesar Trajanus Ö in the month of Kaisareios, on the 12th day, in [Tebtunis in the] division [of Polemon] of the Arsinoite [nome. N.N. agrees] along with Pakebkis Ö on his left Ö priests from Tebtunis Ö [to Kronion son of] Herakleides about ..-seven years old Ö [that they, the agreeing parties have received] from the same Kronion an interest-bearing loan of 240 drachmas [of silver principal] Ö [and that it is incumbent upon] the agreeing parties [to repay] to Kronion the 240 [drachmas of the principal] of the loan [and the] interest in the month of Epeiph of the coming Ö [year] without delay. [And if they fail to repay as] written, [Kronion] shall have the right to Ö for his own Ö year those [parcels of land] in the vicinity of Tebtunis Ö in the so-called LaÖ (here the papyrus breaks off)</ab>
         </div>
